questions.text:
Trace the output of the following code snippet:

```cpp
int x;
double y;
// Input: 10 25.5
cin >> x >> y;
cout << x + y;
```

What will be stored in the variable `ch` after the following code execution?

```cpp
char ch;
// Input:   Z
cin >> ch;
```

*(Note: There are three leading spaces before 'Z')*

Trace the following code. What character is stored in `c2`?

```cpp
char c1, c2;
// Input: A B
cin.get(c1);
cin.get(c2);
```

Given the input `45.67`, what will be the values of `a` and `b` after this code executes?

```cpp
int a;
double b;
cin >> a >> b;
```

What is the output of the following code?

```cpp
string s = "C++ Programming";
cout << s.length();
```

Trace the output of the code below:

```cpp
int x = 4;
cout << pow(x, 0.5);
```

If the user enters `-15 20`, what are the values of `x` and `y`?

```cpp
int x, y;
cin >> x >> y;
```

What happens in the following scenario?

```cpp
int num;
// Input: Hello 5
cin >> num;
```

Trace the values of `ch1` and `ch2`:

```cpp
char ch1, ch2;
// Input: 12
cin >> ch1 >> ch2;
```

Given input `28 32 45`, what is the value of `sum` after these statements?

```cpp
int a, b, c, sum;
cin >> a;
cin >> b;
cin >> c;
sum = a + b + c;
```

Trace the following code snippet. What is stored in `val`?

```cpp
int val;
// Input: 10.99
cin >> val;
```

What is the effect of the following statement?

```cpp
char ch;
// Input: \n (A newline character produced by pressing Enter)
cin.get(ch);
```

Analyze this code. What is output?

```cpp
int a = 5, b = 2;
cout << pow(a, b);
```
